Slice the squid "tube" into Â¼ in (1cm) rings and cut each tentacle in half. Heat the oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Add the garlic and cook, stirring, for 1 minute. Raise the heat to high and add the squid. Cook, stirring, for 3 minutes until the squid looks opaque and is hot. Stir in the lemon juice and paprika, and season with salt. Serve immediately, with lemon wedges for squeezing. 2. Heat the oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Add the garlic and cook, stirring, for 1 minute. Raise the heat to high and add the squid. Cook, stirring, for 3 minutes until the squid looks opaque and is hot. 3. Stir in the lemon juice and paprika, and season with salt.